  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows the graph of a sinusoidal wave with 1 crest and 1 trough in the first and fourth quadrants of the gridded plane. The horizontal axis is labeled “Time, in seconds,” and the numbers 0 through 4, in increments of 1, are indicated. The vertical axis is labeled “Angular Displacement, in radians,” and the numbers negative 0.2 through 0.2, in increments of 0.1, are indicated. The wave begins at the coordinates 0 seconds comma 0.0 radians, has a crest at the coordinates 1 second comma 0.2 radians, crosses the horizontal axis at 2 seconds, has a trough at the coordinates 3 seconds comma negative 0.2 radians, and crosses the horizontal axis at 4 seconds.\" src=\"/images/5ad1e86aa97ad5ca6bca7b6abf913dde.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A simple pendulum is oscillating in simple harmonic motion, and its angular displacement as a function of time is shown in the graph. Which of the following statements about the angular speed and the magnitude of the angular acceleration of the pendulum is correct?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i2",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The angular speed is a maximum at <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1 second\"><math alttext=\"1 second\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>s</mtext></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3 seconds\"><math alttext=\"3 seconds\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>s</mtext></math></span></span>, and the magnitude of the angular acceleration is a maximum at <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0 seconds\"><math alttext=\"0 seconds\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>0</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>s</mtext></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 seconds\"><math alttext=\"2 seconds\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>2</mtext><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>s</mtext></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4 seconds\"><math alttext=\"4 seconds\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>4</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>s</mtext></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The angular speed is a maximum at <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0 seconds\"><math alttext=\"0 seconds\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>0</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>s</mtext></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 seconds\"><math alttext=\"2 seconds\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>2</mtext><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>s</mtext></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4 seconds\"><math alttext=\"4 seconds\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>4</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>s</mtext></math></span></span>, and the magnitude of the angular acceleration is a maximum at <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1 second\"><math alttext=\"1 second\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>s</mtext></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3 seconds\"><math alttext=\"3 seconds\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>s</mtext></math></span></span>.</p>",
